!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = tissue: PBMC
!Sample_characteristics_ch1 = cell type: B cells
!Sample_molecule_ch1 = protein
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = B cells were sorted by magnetic sorting using anti-CD19 beads from PBMC
!Sample_extract_protocol_ch1 = The stained cells were sorted into tetramer+ cells and tetramer neg cells and cells from 4 individuals were pooled to be included in a single gem. Tetramer neg cells were titrated up to a total of 100,000 cells, and then mixed with tetramer+ cells. This cell mixture was resuspended in 2% bovine serum albumin (BSA; Bovogen) in PBS for CITE-seq antibody staining. The cells were incubated with Fc receptor blocker (Miltenyi Biotec) at 4Â°C, and then stained with prepared CITE-seq antibody mixture and incubated at 4Â°C for 30 minutes. Next, the cells were washed 3 times, and resuspended to 1000 cells/Âµl, in a volume of 40â100 Âµl for subsequent library preparation. Transcriptome, antibody-derived tag, and BCR libraries were separately generated using 10X Genomics kits. All samples were sequenced using an Illumina HiSeq 2500, with an average of over 20 million 100-bp paired-end reads.
!Sample_description = Library name: FB_T6_G1
!Sample_description = Feature barcode data (ADT)
!Sample_data_processing = Fastq files were processed using cellranger-6.1.2. References for GEX and BCR are GRCh38-3.0.0 and vdj_GRCh38_alts_ensembl-5.0.0, respectively
!Sample_data_processing = Assembly: GRCh38
!Sample_data_processing = Supplementary files format and content: Tap-separated values files and matrix files
!Sample_data_processing = Library strategy: CITE-seq
